    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Writing utensils containing permanent color dyes, paints, or inks, used to transfer notations, designs, or markings onto fabric materials. The color dyes employed by these tools are especially designed to mantain their color over time after the dye has dried, without significant fading during wash or wear. Also refers to a class of measuring tools or devices used to trace or illustrate textile alteration patterns with onto fabrics, typically with ink or chalk, in preparation for subsequent alteration activities.</Note_Text>
